docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s national security adviser, John R. Bolton, fleshed out his boss’s “America First” foreign policy on Monday, disparaging an international organization vilified by conservatives and reaffirming a pro-Israel tilt by announcing the closing of the Palestine Liberation Organization’s office in Washington. But on one of Mr. Trump’s signature projects, nuclear diplomacy with North Korea, he parted company.
